This paper discusses the statistical analysis of scientific-publication data, which falls under the field of scientometrics. The paper specifically analyzes the download and citation statistics of a physics journal, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses correlations between different processes, which could be related to social networks and information systems (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the popularity of a publication, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR).
